.TH CMatrix 1 "Mon May 3 1999"
.SH NAME
CMatrix
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cmatrix
[\-abcfhlohnsmV] [\-F fps] [\-T color] [\-H color] [\-O color]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shows a scrolling 'Matrix' like screen in Linux.
.PP
Rendering uses Notcurses (24-bit color, UTF-8). Build and run-time require \fBlibnotcurses\fR (e.g. Debian: \fBlibnotcurses-dev\fR).
.PP
Default rain uses Unicode PUA \fBU+E000\fR–\fBU+E069\fR (106 glyphs) from a merged DejaVu font. \fBmake install\fR installs \fIDejaVuSansMono_working.ttf\fR as \fIDejaVuSansMono.ttf\fR into \fI/usr/share/fonts/truetype/\fR and runs \fBfc-cache\fR. User-local install path is \fI~/.local/share/fonts/DejaVuSansMono.ttf\fR. Set your terminal font to \fIDejaVu Sans Mono\fR so those code points render correctly.
.PP
For Japanese mode (\-c), the build may still install Matrix Code fonts system-wide; set your terminal to "Matrix Code" for \-c, or use Matrix Code NFI (DaFont). Console mode (\-l) uses setfont/consolechars; install a console font separately for \-l.
.SS OPTIONS
.TP
.I "\-a"
Asynchronous scroll
.TP
.I "\-b"
Bold characters on
.TP
.I "\-B"
All bold characters (overrides \-b)
.TP
.I "\-f"
Force the linux $TERM type to be on
.TP
.I "\-l"
Linux mode (uses setfont/consolechars; install a console font for \-l)
.TP
.I "\-o"
Use old-style scrolling
.TP
.I "\-c"
Japanese mode: draws Matrix Code glyphs (32 half-width Katakana + 95 Basic Latin, one column each) using the wide-character API. Requires UTF-8 locale and a font with those glyphs (Matrix Code is installed by the build). Set
.B CMATRIX_ASCII_FALLBACK=1
to use ASCII placeholders instead.
.TP
.I "\-L"
Locks cmatrix, Unable to quit
.TP
.I "\-h, \-?"
Print usage and exit
.TP
.I "\-k"
Every characters change 
.TP
.I "\-n"
No bold characters (overrides \-b)
.TP
.I "\-s"
"Screensaver" mode, exits on first keystroke
.TP
.I "\-V"
Print version information and exit
.TP
.I "\-F fps"
Frame rate in frames per second, 1–120 (default ~23.976; e.g. 60 for high refresh).
.TP
.I "\-T color"
Use this color for matrix tail (default green).
Argument is a named color (see
.B \-h
list) or truecolor
.I #RRGGBB
with a leading \fB#\fR (e.g. \fB#00ff41\fR).
.TP
.I "\-H color"
Use this color for the drop head (default #c3ffbf).
Same rules as
.BR \-T .
.TP
.I "\-O color"
Use this color for the \-M message (default red).
Same rules as
.BR \-T .
.TP
.I "\-M message"
Add a message in the center of cmatrix
.SS KEYSTROKES
The following keystrokes are available during execution (unavailable in
\-s mode)
.TP
.I "a"
Toggle asynchronous scroll
.TP
.I "b"
Random bold characters
.TP
.I "n"
Turn off bold characters
.TP
.I "! @ # $ % ^ & )"
Change the color of the matrix to the corresponding color:
! \- red, @ \- green, # \- yellow, $ \- blue, % \- magenta, ^ \- cyan,
& \- white, ) \- black.
.TP
.I "q"
Quit the program
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CMATRIX_ASCII_FALLBACK
If set, \fB\-c\fR always uses ASCII placeholders (#0-9A-F).
.TP
.B TERM
If \fBTERM\fR is \fIdumb\fR or unset, \fB\-c\fR is disabled and a warning is printed.
.SH FONTS FOR JAPANESE MODE (\-c)
Japanese mode uses 32 half-width Katakana and 95 Basic Latin code points (all single-column). The build installs Matrix Code (TrueType) to the fontconfig dir; set your terminal to "Matrix Code". Cmatrix cannot change your terminal font (only \fB\-l\fR console mode loads a font via setfont).
.RS
.IP "Matrix Code (installed)" 4
Installed by \fBmake install\fR to e.g. /usr/share/fonts/truetype/cmatrix/. Set your terminal font to "Matrix Code" for \-c.
.IP "Matrix Code NFI (DaFont)" 4
Optional. Download from https://www.dafont.com/matrix-code-nfi.font and install; set terminal to "Matrix Code NFI".
.IP "Testing your font" 4
Paste in your terminal: \fIｱｲｳｴｵｶｷｸｹｺｻｼｽｾｿ\fR. If you see boxes or replacement characters, the font does not have half-width Katakana.
.RE
.SH BUGS
This program is very CPU intensive.  Don't be surprised if it eats up over
40% of your CPU at times.
